            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34890",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmuir",
                        "name": "dmuir",
                        "displayName": "David Muir",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Patched Zend_Validate_Db_Abstract with new getter method",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmuir",
                        "name": "dmuir",
                        "displayName": "David Muir",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-24T19:14:09.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-24T19:14:09.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34914",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Patch unusable.\nAdded feature as part of another on with r18417",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-25T11:44:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-25T11:44:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35068",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmuir",
                        "name": "dmuir",
                        "displayName": "David Muir",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Although  r18417 added a getter\/setter for the adapter, it would be more useful to let the getter have a default fallback like there is in the _query method. Otherwise each extensions requiring the adapter needs to duplicate that part of the query method, which is the reason why I raised the issue in the first place.\n\nCould you give me a reason why my patch was rejected? Would be helpful for future contributions.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmuir",
                        "name": "dmuir",
                        "displayName": "David Muir",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-04T21:48:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-04T21:48:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35079",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Your \"patch\" did not conform the API.\nWhen you add a getter you must also add a setter.\nWhen you do this for one option you should also do this for all other options, not only for a single one.\n\nRelated to _query:\ngetAdapter return only what has been set. A default adapter is not set by the user, so it's not returned by getAdapter. And the adapter option can also be optional or set afterwards. So it is not filled per default.\n\nExtending classes will not have to duplicate the adapter code, but simply use\/extend _query for their own purposes.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-05T11:39:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-05T11:39:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35084",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmuir",
                        "name": "dmuir",
                        "displayName": "David Muir",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "But that's precisely the point. You cannot have an extension use the default adapter prior to querying without :\n1. Duplicating the \"get default adapter\" code in _query()\nor\n2. Providing a getter for it ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmuir",
                        "name": "dmuir",
                        "displayName": "David Muir",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-05T19:07:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-05T19:07:22.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
